# Deobfuscated Code & Explanation

## Deobfuscated Version

```javascript
// Constants
var TAU = 6.283;           // ≈ 2π
var PHI = 1.618;           // Golden ratio
var SQRT_HALF = 0.707;     // ≈ √(1/2)

// Configuration parameters
var config = {
    repulsionStrength: 4000,    // parameterA - repulsion force between nodes
    springConstant: 0.004,       // parameterB - default spring constant
    damping: 0.92,               // parameterC - velocity damping factor
    gravityStrength: 0.0003,     // constantD - pull toward center
    particleLimit: 40,           // limitE - max number of particles
    rateF: 0.04,                 // particle drag/friction
    cameraSmoothing: 0.06        // valueG - camera interpolation speed
};

// Nodes in a force-directed graph
var nodes = [
    { id: "hub",       label: "Hub",        r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "alpha",     label: "Alpha",      r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "beta",      label: "Beta",       r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "gamma",     label: "Gamma",      r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "delta",     label: "Delta",      r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "epsilon",   label: "Epsilon",    r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// Edges (springs) connecting nodes
var edges = [
    { a: "hub", b: "alpha",   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: "hub", b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: "hub", b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub", b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub", b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "beta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "gamma", b: "delta",   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera system
var camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// Particle system
var particles = [];
var frameCount = 0;

// Find a node by its ID
function findNode(id) {
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// Physics simulation step
function simulatePhysics() {
    // 1. Node-to-node REPULSION (Coulomb's law style)
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (var j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            var dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            var dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            var force = config.repulsionStrength / (dist * dist);
            var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            var fy = (dy / dist) * force;

            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // 2. Edge SPRING forces (Hooke's law)
    for (var e = 0; e < edges.length; e++) {
        var nodeA = findNode(edges[e].a);
        var nodeB = findNode(edges[e].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;

        var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        var displacement = dist - edges[e].rest;
        var force = (edges[e].k || config.springConstant) * displacement;

        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // 3. Apply DAMPING, GRAVITY toward center (400, 300), and update positions
    for (var n = 0; n < nodes.length; n++) {
        nodes[n].vx += (400 - nodes[n].x) * config.gravityStrength;
        nodes[n].vy += (300 - nodes[n].y) * config.gravityStrength;
        nodes[n].vx *= config.damping;
        nodes[n].vy *= config.damping;
        nodes[n].x += nodes[n].vx;
        nodes[n].y += nodes[n].vy;
    }
}

// Spawn a particle from a random node
function spawnParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= config.particleLimit) return;

    var sourceNode = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;

    particles.push({
        x: sourceNode.x,
        y: sourceNode.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT_HALF
    });
}

// Update and cull particles
function updateParticles() {
    for (var i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        var p = particles[i];
        p.vx *= 1 - config.rateF * 0.125;
        p.vy *= 1 - config.rateF * 0.125;
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
            particles.splice(i, 1);
        }
    }
}

// Smoothly interpolate camera toward target
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.cameraSmoothing;
    camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.cameraSmoothing;
    camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.cameraSmoothing;
}

// Main loop tick
function tick() {
    simulatePhysics();
    updateParticles();
    updateCamera();
    if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
    frameCount++;
}

// Run at ~60fps (16ms interval)
setInterval(tick, 16);
```

---

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph simulation** with a particle system — the kind of thing you'd see in a network visualization. Here's the breakdown:

### 🔵 Force-Directed Graph Layout
- **6 nodes** ("Hub", "Alpha", "Beta", "Gamma", "Delta", "Epsilon") connected by **8 edges**
- Uses classic physics-based layout:
  - **Repulsion**: All nodes repel each other (inverse-square law, like electric charges)
  - **Spring attraction**: Connected nodes are pulled together by springs with rest lengths (Hooke's law)
  - **Gravity**: Gentle pull toward center point (400, 300)
  - **Damping**: Velocity is multiplied by 0.92 each frame to prevent oscillation

### ✨ Particle System
- Every 3 frames, a **particle spawns** from a random node
- Particles drift outward with friction, aging until they die (800–2000 frames)
- Capped at **40 particles** max
- Creates a visual "aura" or "energy" effect around nodes

### 🎥 Camera
- Smooth camera interpolation (lerp at 6% per frame) toward a target position/zoom
- Ready for panning/zooming interaction (though no input handlers are in this snippet)

### 🕐 Runs at ~60fps
- `setInterval(tick, 16)` drives the whole simulation

**In essence**: This is the physics engine behind an animated, interactive network graph visualization — likely rendered elsewhere on a canvas. The obfuscation was purely to hide this relatively straightforward simulation logic.
